ABUJA – The latest update from the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control(NCDC) show that the coronavirus pandemic has claimed the lives of 103 Nigerians since the index case was recorded in February in Lagos. According to a post shared on Twitter late on Wednesday night, Nigeria recorded 195 new infections. In all, 534 patients have been discharged. Lagos remains the epicentre with 82 out of the 195 new cases. This is followed by Kano with 30 new cases. The breakdown is as follows: 195 new cases of #COVID19; 82-Lagos30-Kano19-Zamfara18-Sokoto10-Borno9-FCT8-Oyo5-Kebbi5-Gombe4-Ogun3-Katsina1-Kaduna1-Adamawa 3,145 confirmed cases of #COVID19 in NigeriaDischarged: 534Deaths: 103 ABUJA - The number of confirmed Coronavirus cases in Nigeria on Tuesday went steep high with the addition of 195 cases, the highest in a single day since the pandemic made its debut in Nigeria in February. According to the NCDC report on its Twitter handle @NCDCgov, Lagos, which is… April 29, 2020 In "Top Stories" The Nigerian Centre for Disease Control has announced 34 new confirmed covid19 cases in the country. new cases Nigeria’s Coronavirus Cases Jumps To 407 With 34 New Cases Nigeria has recorded another 34 new cases of Coronavirus, with the total figures jumping to 407. According to the Nigerian Centre for… April 16, 2020 In "News" Nigeria’s coronavirus cases have increased to 318 after 13 new cases were recorded. The Nigeria Control for Disease Control made this known via its Twitter handle on Saturday. "13 new cases of #COVID19 have been reported; 11 in Lagos, 1 in Delta & 1 in Kano "As at 9:30pm 11th… April 12, 2020 In "News"